code_changes.content:
{
  "buggy_files": [
    "drivers/ata/libata-core.c"
  ],
  "buggy_functions": [
    "ata_device_blacklist"
  ],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Samsung 860 EVO SSD has issues with queued TRIM commands (SEND FPDMA QUEUED timeout) when used with certain SATA controllers. The kernel already has a device blacklist mechanism in the `ata_device_blacklist` array in drivers/ata/libata-core.c that allows disabling queued TRIM for problematic devices using the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag. This flag is checked at line 2218 in the ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv function to disable queued TRIM support. Similar devices like Samsung SSD 840* (line 4562-4563) and Samsung SSD 850* (line 4564-4565) already have entries in this blacklist. The Samsung 860 EVO is missing from this list and needs an entry added with the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM and ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM flags, similar to the existing Samsung 840/850 entries."
}

